-- Qualcomm to Help Scartel to Start Voice Service, Kommersant Says
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-04-12T04:53:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/qualcomm-to-help-scartel-to-start-voice-service-kommersant-says.html
Qualcomm Inc. (QCOM) , the world’s biggest
maker of mobile-phone chips, will help Russia’s LTE wireless
network operator Scartel to start voice communications,
 Kommersant  said today, citing people it didn’t identify.  Scartel produces and sells devices for mobile access to the
Internet but wants to be able to support voice services, the
newspaper said. Qualcomm will be supplying chips, which can work
in 3G and 4G networks, newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
 yfedorinova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  